# Accessibility Heuristics

## Landmarks

- Use proper landmarks and labels: `role="navigation" aria-label="Primary"` for main nav; `header`, `main`, `footer` where applicable.

## Focus

- Use `focus-ring` utility for interactive elements; ensure keyboard reachability for all actions.

## Labels

- Inputs must have visible labels or `aria-label`/`aria-labelledby`.
- Buttons with only icons should include `aria-label` and/or visible label nearby.

## Contrast & Theme

- Ensure sufficient contrast in both light and dark modes using theme tokens.

## Motion

- Respect `prefers-reduced-motion`; timings come from CSS variables already wired in `style.css`.
